               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350921-name-590" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350921-name-590" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350921-name-590" type="surname" value="PARVER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350921-name-590" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS PARVER</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep a coffee-shop in High-street, Islington. On the night of the 17th of September, there was an alarm of a coat being lost—I heard the door shut, ran out, and saw the prisoner six or eight doors off with the coat, which he dropped, after running six or eight doors further—I lost sight of him, but to the best of my knowledge he is the man—he also threw away a pair of my shoes, which I had placed at the foot of the stairs about two or three o'clock that afternoon—the prisoner had been taking coffee in the house, and paid for it.</p>
               <p>
